news.title: Land acquisition in NCR getting difficult for developers
news.para: This comes at a time when demand for new homes has picked up after the Covid-19-led slump and most units in under-construction and completed projects have already been sold.

news.title: Aurangabad: No eviction relief for Labour Colony residents from HC
news.para: On May 6, the two-member bench comprising Justice R D Dhanuka and Justice S G Mehare directed the petitioners and other occupants of the colony to hand over “peaceful and vacant possession” of their respective structures to the Aurangabad collector on or before 11 am on May 10.

news.title: Tamil Nadu introduces apartment redevelopment bill
news.para: Introducing the Tamil Nadu Apartment Ownership Bill, 2022, housing minister S Muthusamy said “The new legislation was introduced to safeguard the interest of the apartment owners as well as improve the administration of common areas and facilities.”

news.title: Over Rs 2,160 crore collected as stamp duty in Raigad district
news.para: ​As per figures made available by the assistant collector of stamp duty collection, the target for the year was Rs 1,880 crore, which was surpassed.

news.title: Macrotech to invest Rs 3,800 crore in FY23 on construction of realty projects: MD
news.para: Macrotech Developers MD and CEO Abhishek Lodha said: "We spent about Rs 2,600 crore on construction last fiscal year. Our construction spend is estimated at Rs 3,800 crore during the current fiscal."

news.title: HDFC hikes lending rate by 30 bps
news.para: "HDFC increases its Retail Prime Lending Rate (RPLR) on housing loans, on which its Adjustable Rate Home Loans (ARHL) are benchmarked, by 30 basis points, with effect from May 9, 2022," the housing finance company said in a statement.

news.title: Indian Bank revises repo linked lending rate
news.para: The bank's move comes after a number of banks raised their external benchmark based lending rates following an increase of 0.40 per cent in the repo rate -- at which the Reserve Bank lends short term money to banks.

news.title: IIT-Delhi team investigates Chintels Paradiso cave-in site
news.para: Last week, the district administration and the department of town and country planning (DTCP) appointed a structural engineer and a valuer to conduct an audit separate from the IIT-Delhi team and issued a work order. Both have started work.

news.title: Admin launches probe; colony is illegal, says Indore collector
news.para: According to IMC Commissioner Pratibha Pal, the civic body was responsible for extending infrastructure-related assistance to fire department.

news.title: Rustomjee Developers paid Rs 28 crore premium for land deal: Mumbai suburban collector
news.para: ​​BJP MLA Ashish Shelar had alleged that the transaction was a Rs 1,000-crore scam.

news.title: Builders liable to clear tax before flat registration: Kolkata civic body
news.para: A KMC assessment department official said a section of promoters kept the land owner with whom they enter into agreement to develop a residential building in the dark about the property tax payable to KMC during the intervening period.

news.title: Pre-1991 structure doesn't make new building in CRZ legal: NGT
news.para: The tribunal stated that it is not willing to accept the violator’s argument supporting the constructions because a structure existed at the location prior to 1991.

news.title: NGT slaps Rs 60 crore fine on Savfab Buildtech for flouting environment norms
news.para: The National Green Tribunal (NGT) has slapped a steep fine of Rs 60.23 crore on a developer for flouting various environment norms in its residential project in Ghaziabad.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad development body launches fourth phase of demolition drive
news.para: HDUDA chief and a team of officials led the demolition drive in Unkal. This time around, HDUDA roped in police protection, deploying more police personnel.

news.title: Building plan must be displayed at entrance of new construction sites in Chennai
news.para: In an internal circular, chief engineer (planning) P Duraisamy has said presently not all constructions have building plans displayed at the site.
